    {
      "id": "3e1f2b63-48f9-4fee-8ce1-b65ff369cc79",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The authors collect data from 12 BLearning courses and summarized 3 grading policies. Courses where the grading policy was lenient were more likely to cause the illusion of highly accurate predictive models. Authors also discuss the effectiveness of a lenient grading policy altogether.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "3e1f2b63-48f9-4fee-8ce1-b65ff369cc79",
        "parent": {
